n info available\\\")\\n    22→\\n    23→// ErrNotTaskCheckpoint is returned when a rewind point is not a task checkpoint.\\n    24→var ErrNotTaskCheckpoint = errors.New(\\\"not a task checkpoint\\\")\\n    25→\\n    26→// ErrEmptyRepository is returned when the repository has no commits yet.\\n    27→var ErrEmptyRepository = errors.New(\\\"repository has no commits yet\\\")\\n    28→\\n    29→// SessionInfo contains information about the current session state.\\n    30→// This is used to generate trailers for linking commits to their AI session.\\n    31→type SessionInfo struct {\\n    32→\\t// SessionID is the session identifier extracted from the latest commit's metadata\\n    33→\\tSessionID string\\n    34→\\n    35→\\t// Reference is a strategy-specific reference string.\\n    36→\\t// For manual-commit strategy: \\\"entire/abc1234\\\" (the shadow branch name)\\n    37→\\t// Empty for commit strategy (metadata is in the same commit).\\n    38→\\tReference string\\n    39→\\n    40→\\t// CommitHash is the full SHA of the commit containing the session metadata.\\n    41→\\t// Empty for commit strategy.\\n    42→\\tCommitHash string\\n    43→}\\n    44→\\n    45→// RewindPoint represents a point to which the user can rewind.\\n    46→// This abstraction allows different strategies to use different\\n    47→// identifiers (commit hashes, branch names, stash refs, etc.)\\n    48→type RewindPoint struct {\\n    49→\\t// ID is the unique identifier for this rewind point\\n    50→\\t// (commit hash, branch name, stash ref, etc.)\\n    51→\\tID string\\n    52→\\n    53→\\t// Message is the human-readable description/summary\\n    54→\\tMessage string\\n    55→\\n    56→\\t// MetadataDir is the path to the metadata directory\\n    57→\\tMetadataDir string\\n    58→\\n    59→\\t// Date is when this rewind point was created\\n    60→\\tDate time.Time\\n    61→\\n    62→\\t// IsTaskCheckpoint indicates if this is a task checkpoint (vs a session checkpoint)\\n    63→\\tIsTaskCheckpoint bool\\n    64→\\n    65→\\t// ToolUseID is the tool use ID for task checkpoints (empty for session checkpoints)\\n    66→\\tToolUseID string\\n    67→\\n    68→\\t// IsLogsOnly indicates this is a commit with session logs but no shadow branch state.\\n    69→\\t// The logs can be restored from entire/checkpoints/v1, but file state requires git checkout.\\n    70→\\tIsLogsOnly bool\\n    71→\\n    72→\\t// CheckpointID is the stable 12-hex-char identifier for logs-only points.\\n    73→\\t// Used to retrieve logs from entire/checkpoints/v1/<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/full.jsonl\\n    74→\\t// Empty for shadow branch checkpoints (uncommitted).\\n    75→\\tCheckpointID id.CheckpointID\\n    76→\\n    77→\\t// Agent is the human-readable name of the agent that created this checkpoint\\n    78→\\t// (e.g., \\\"Claude Code\\\", \\\"Cursor IDE\\\")\\n    79→\\tAgent agent.AgentType\\n    80→\\n    81→\\t// SessionID is the session identifier for this checkpoint.\\n    82→\\t// Used to distinguish checkpoints from different concurrent sessions.\\n    83→\\tSessionID string\\n    84→\\n    85→\\t// SessionPrompt is the initial prompt that started this session.\\n    86→\\t// Used to help users identify which session a checkpoint belongs to.\\n    87→\\tSessionPrompt string\\n    88→\\n    89→\\t// SessionCount is the number of sessions in this checkpoint (1 for single-session).\\n    90→\\t// Only populated for logs-only points with multi-session checkpoints.\\n    91→\\tSessionCount int\\n    92→\\n    93→\\t// SessionIDs contains all session IDs when this is a multi-session checkpoint.\\n    94→\\t// The last entry is the most recent session (same as SessionID).\\n    95→\\t// Only populated for logs-only points with multi-session checkpoints.\\n    96→\\tSessionIDs []string\\n    97→\\n    98→\\t// SessionPrompts contains the first prompt for each session (parallel to SessionIDs).\\n    99→\\t// Used to display context when showing resume commands for multi-session checkpoints.\\n   100→\\tSessionPrompts []string\\n   101→}\\n   102→\\n   103→// RewindPreview describes what will happen when rewinding to a checkpoint.\\n   104→// Used to warn users about files that will be modified or deleted.\\n   105→type RewindPreview struct {\\n   106→\\t// FilesToRestore are files from the checkpoint that will be written/restored.\\n   107→\\tFilesToRestore []string\\n   108→\\n   109→\\t// FilesToDelete are untracked files that will be removed.\\n   110→\\t// These are files created after the checkpoint that aren't in the checkpoint tree\\n   111→\\t// and weren't present at session start.\\n   112→\\tFilesToDelete []string\\n   113→\\n   114→\\t// TrackedChanges are tracked files with uncommitted changes that will be reverted.\\n   115→\\t// These come from the existing CanRewind() warning.\\n   116→\\tTrackedChanges []string\\n   117→}\\n   118→\\n   119→// StepContext contains all information needed for saving a step checkpoint.\\n   120→// All file paths should be pre-filtered and normalized by the CLI layer.\\n   121→type StepContext struct {\\n   122→\\t// SessionID is the Claude Code session identifier\\n   123→\\tSessionID string\\n   124→\\n   125→\\t// ModifiedFiles is the list of files modified during the session\\n   126→\\t// (extracted from the transcript, already filtered and relative)\\n   127→\\tModifiedFiles []string\\n   128→\\n   129→\\t// NewFiles is the list of new files created during the session\\n   130→\\t// (pre-computed by CLI from pre-prompt state comparison)\\n   131→\\tNewFiles []string\\n   132→\\n   133→\\t// DeletedFiles is the list of files deleted during the session\\n   134→\\t// (tracked files that no longer exist)\\n   135→\\tDeletedFiles []string\\n   136→\\n   137→\\t// MetadataDir is the path to the session metadata directory\\n   138→\\tMetadataDir string\\n   139→\\n   140→\\t// MetadataDirAbs is the absolute path to the session metadata directory\\n   141→\\tMetadataDirAbs string\\n   142→\\n   143→\\t// CommitMessage is the generated commit message\\n   144→\\tCommitMessage string\\n   145→\\n   146→\\t// TranscriptPath is the path to the transcript file\\n   147→\\tTranscriptPath string\\n   148→\\n   149→\\t// AuthorName is the name to use for commits\\n   150→\\tAuthorName string\\n   151→\\n   152→\\t// AuthorEmail is the email to use for commits\\n   153→\\tAuthorEmail string\\n   154→\\n   155→\\t// AgentType is the human-readable agent name (e.g., \\\"Claude Code\\\", \\\"Cursor IDE\\\")\\n   156→\\tAgentType agent.AgentType\\n   157→\\n   158→\\t// Transcript position at step/turn start - tracks what was added during this step\\n   159→\\tStepTranscriptIdentifier string // Last identifier when step started (UUID for Claude, message ID for Gemini)\\n   160→\\tStepTranscriptStart      int    // Transcript line count when this step/turn started\\n   161→\\n   162→\\t// TokenUsage contains the token usage for this checkpoint\\n   163→\\tTokenUsage *agent.TokenUsage\\n   164→}\\n   165→\\n   166→// TaskStepContext contains all information needed for saving a task step checkpoint.\\n   167→// This is called by the PostToolUse[Task] hook when a subagent completes.\\n   168→// The strategy is responsible for creating metadata structures and storing them\\n   169→// according to its storage approach.\\n   170→type TaskStepContext struct {\\n   171→\\t// SessionID is the Claude Code session identifier\\n   172→\\tSessionID string\\n   173→\\n   174→\\t// ToolUseID is the unique identifier for this Task tool invocation\\n   175→\\tToolUseID string\\n   176→\\n   177→\\t// AgentID is the subagent identifier (from tool_response.agentId)\\n   178→\\tAgentID string\\n   179→\\n   180→\\t// ModifiedFiles is the list of files modified by the subagent\\n   181→\\t// (extracted from the subagent's transcript)\\n   182→\\tModifiedFiles []string\\n   183→\\n   184→\\t// NewFiles is the list of new files created by the subagent\\n   185→\\t// (computed from pre-task state comparison)\\n   186→\\tNewFiles []string\\n   187→\\n   188→\\t// DeletedFiles is the list of files deleted by the subagent\\n   189→\\tDeletedFiles []string\\n   190→\\n   191→\\t// TranscriptPath is the path to the main session transcript\\n   192→\\tTranscriptPath string\\n   193→\\n   194→\\t// SubagentTranscriptPath is the path to the subagent's transcript (if available)\\n   195→\\tSubagentTranscriptPath string\\n   196→\\n   197→\\t// CheckpointUUID is the UUID for transcript truncation when rewinding\\n   198→\\tCheckpointUUID string\\n   199→\\n   200→\\t// AuthorName is the name to use for commits\\n   201→\\tAuthorName string\\n   202→\\n   203→\\t// AuthorEmail is the email to use for commits\\n   204→\\tAuthorEmail string\\n   205→\\n   206→\\t// IsIncremental indicates this is an incremental checkpoint during task execution,\\n   207→\\t// not a final task completion checkpoint. When true:\\n   208→\\t// - Writes to checkpoints/NNN-{tool-use-id}.json instead of checkpoint.json\\n   209→\\t// - Skips transcript handling\\n   210→\\t// - Uses incremental commit message\\n   211→\\tIsIncremental bool\\n   212→\\n   213→\\t// IncrementalSequence is the checkpoint sequence number (1, 2, 3, ...)\\n   214→\\t// Only used when IsIncremental is true\\n   215→\\tIncrementalSequence int\\n   216→\\n   217→\\t// IncrementalType is the tool that triggered this checkpoint (\\\"TodoWrite\\\", \\\"Edit\\\", etc.)\\n   218→\\t// Only used when IsIncremental is true\\n   219→\\tIncrementalType string\\n   220→\\n   221→\\t// IncrementalData is the tool_input payload for this checkpoint\\n   222→\\t// Only used when IsIncremental is true\\n   223→\\tIncrementalData json.RawMessage\\n   224→\\n   225→\\t// SubagentType is the type of subagent (e.g., \\\"dev\\\", \\\"reviewer\\\")\\n   226→\\t// Extracted from tool_input.subagent_type in Task tool\\n   227→\\t// Used for descriptive commit messages\\n   228→\\tSubagentType string\\n   229→\\n   230→\\t// TaskDescription is the task description provided to the subagent\\n   231→\\t// Extracted from tool_input.description in Task tool\\n   232→\\t// Used for descriptive commit messages\\n   233→\\tTaskDescription string\\n   234→\\n   235→\\t// TodoContent is the content of the in-progress todo item\\n   236→\\t// Extracted from tool_input.todos where status == \\\"in_progress\\\"\\n   237→\\t// Used for descriptive incremental checkpoint messages\\n   238→\\tTodoContent string\\n   239→\\n   240→\\t// AgentType is the human-readable agent name (e.g., \\\"Claude Code\\\", \\\"Cursor IDE\\\")\\n   241→\\tAgentType agent.AgentType\\n   242→}\\n   243→\\n   244→// TaskCheckpoint contains the checkpoint information written to checkpoint.json\\n   245→type TaskCheckpoint struct {\\n   246→\\tSessionID      string `json:\\\"session_id\\\"`\\n   247→\\tToolUseID      string `json:\\\"tool_use_id\\\"`\\n   248→\\tCheckpointUUID string `json:\\\"checkpoint_uuid\\\"`\\n   249→\\tAgentID        string `json:\\\"agent_id,omitempty\\\"`\\n   250→}\\n   251→\\n   252→// SubagentCheckpoint represents an intermediate checkpoint created during subagent execution.\\n   253→// These are created by PostToolUse hooks for tools like TodoWrite, Edit, Write.\\n   254→type SubagentCheckpoint struct {\\n   255→\\tType      string          `json:\\\"type\\\"`        // Tool name: \\\"TodoWrite\\\", \\\"Edit\\\", \\\"Write\\\"\\n   256→\\tToolUseID string          `json:\\\"tool_use_id\\\"` // The tool use ID that created this checkpoint\\n   257→\\tTimestamp time.Time       `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`   // When the checkpoint was created\\n   258→\\tData      json.RawMessage `json:\\\"data\\\"`        // Type-specific payload (tool_input)\\n   259→}\\n   260→\\n   261→// TaskMetadataDir returns the path to a task's metadata directory\\n   262→// within the session metadata directory.\\n   263→func TaskMetadataDir(sessionMetadataDir, toolUseID string) string {\\n   264→\\treturn sessionMetadataDir + \\\"/tasks/\\\" + toolUseID\\n   265→}\\n   266→\\n   267→// ReadTaskCheckpoint reads the checkpoint.json file from a task metadata directory.\\n   268→// This is used during rewind to get the checkpoint UUID for transcript truncation.\\n   269→func ReadTaskCheckpoint(taskMetadataDir string) (*TaskCheckpoint, error) {\\n   270→\\tcheckpointFile := taskMetadataDir + \\\"/checkpoint.json\\\"\\n   271→\\n   272→\\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(checkpointFile) //nolint:gosec // Reading from controlled git metadata path\\n   273→\\tif err != nil {\\n   274→\\t\\treturn nil, err //nolint:wrapcheck // already present in codebase\\n   275→\\t}\\n   276→\\n   277→\\tvar checkpoint TaskCheckpoint\\n   278→\\tif err := json.Unmarshal(data, &checkpoint); err != nil {\\n   279→\\t\\treturn nil, err //nolint:wrapcheck // already present in codebase\\n   280→\\t}\\n   281→\\n   282→\\treturn &checkpoint, nil\\n   283→}\\n   284→\\n   285→// Strategy defines the interface for git operation strategies.\\n   286→// Different implementations can use commits, branches, stashes, etc.\\n   287→//\\n   288→// Note: State capture (tracking untracked files before a session) is handled\\n   289→// by the CLI layer, not the strategy. The strategy receives pre-computed\\n   290→// file lists in StepContext.\\n   291→type Strategy interface {\\n   292→\\t// Name returns the strategy identifier (e.g., \\\"commit\\\", \\\"branch\\\", \\\"stash\\\")\\n   293→\\tName() string\\n   294→\\n   295→\\t// ValidateRepository checks if the repository is in a valid state\\n   296→\\t// for this strategy to operate. Returns an error if validation fails.\\n   297→\\tValidateRepository() error\\n   298→\\n   299→\\t// SaveStep is called on Stop to save all session changes\\n   300→\\t// using this strategy's approach (commit, branch, stash, etc.)\\n   301→\\tSaveStep(ctx context.Context, step StepContext) error\\n   302→\\n   303→\\t// SaveTaskStep is called by PostToolUse[Task] hook when a subagent completes.\\n   304→\\t// Creates a checkpoint commit with task metadata for later rewind.\\n   305→\\t// Commits to shadow branch for later condensation.\\n   306→\\tSaveTaskStep(ctx context.Context, step TaskStepContext) error\\n   307→\\n   308→\\t// GetRewindPoints returns available points to rewind to.\\n   309→\\t// The limit parameter controls the maximum number of points to return.\\n   310→\\tGetRewindPoints(ctx context.Context, limit int) ([]RewindPoint, error)\\n   311→\\n   312→\\t// Rewind restores the repository to the given rewind point.\\n   313→\\t// The metadataDir in the point is used to restore the session transcript.\\n   314→\\tRewind(ctx context.Context, point RewindPoint) error\\n   315→\\n   316→\\t// CanRewind checks if rewinding is currently possible.\\n   317→\\t// Returns (canRewind, reason if not, error)\\n   318→\\tCanRewind(ctx context.Context) (bool, string, error)\\n   319→\\n   320→\\t// PreviewRewind returns what will happen if rewinding to the given point.\\n   321→\\t// This allows showing warnings about files that will be deleted before the rewind.\\n   322→\\t// Returns nil if preview is not supported\\n   323→\\tPreviewRewind(ctx context.Context, point RewindPoint) (*RewindPreview, error)\\n   324→\\n   325→\\t// GetTaskCheckpoint returns the task checkpoint for a given rewind point.\\n   326→\\t// For strategies that store checkpoints on disk (commit, manual-commit), this reads from the filesystem.\\n   327→\\t// Returns nil, nil if not a task checkpoint or checkpoint not found.\\n   328→\\tGetTaskCheckpoint(ctx context.Context, point RewindPoint) (*TaskCheckpoint, error)\\n   329→\\n   330→\\t// GetTaskCheckpointTranscript returns the session transcript for a task checkpoint.\\n   331→\\t// For strategies that store transcripts on disk (commit, manual-commit), this reads from the filesystem.\\n   332→\\tGetTaskCheckpointTranscript(ctx context.Context, point RewindPoint) ([]byte, error)\\n   333→\\n   334→\\t// GetSessionInfo returns session information for linking commits.\\n   335→\\t// This is used by the context command to generate trailers.\\n   336→\\t// Returns ErrNoSession if no session info is available.\\n   337→\\tGetSessionInfo(ctx context.Context) (*SessionInfo, error)\\n   338→\\n   339→\\t// NOTE: ListSessions and GetSession are standalone functions in session.go.\\n   340→\\t// They read from entire/checkpoints/v1 and merge with SessionSource if implemented.\\n   341→\\n   342→\\t// GetMetadataRef returns a reference to the metadata commit for the given checkpoint.\\n   343→\\t// Format: \\\"<branch>@<commit-sha>\\\" (e.g., \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1@abc123\\\").\\n   344→\\t// Returns empty string if not applicable (e.g., commit strategy with filesystem metadata).\\n   345→\\tGetMetadataRef(ctx context.Context, checkpoint Checkpoint) string\\n   346→\\n   347→\\t// GetSessionMetadataRef returns a reference to the most recent metadata commit for a session.\\n   348→\\t// Format: \\\"<branch>@<commit-sha>\\\" (e.g., \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1@abc123\\\").\\n   349→\\t// Returns empty string if not applicable or session not found.\\n   350→\\tGetSessionMetadataRef(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) string\\n   351→\\n   352→\\t// GetSessionContext returns the context.md content for a session.\\n   353→\\t// Returns empty string if not available.\\n   354→\\tGetSessionContext(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) string\\n   355→\\n   356→\\t// GetCheckpointLog returns the session transcript for a specific checkpoint.\\n   357→\\t// For strategies that store transcripts in git branches (manual-commit),\\n   358→\\t// this reads from the checkpoint's commit tree.\\n   359→\\t// For strategies that store on disk (commit), reads from the filesystem.\\n   360→\\t// Returns ErrNoMetadata if transcript is not available.\\n   361→\\tGetCheckpointLog(ctx context.Context, checkpoint Checkpoint) ([]byte, error)\\n   362→\\t// InitializeSession creates session state for a new session.\\n   363→\\t// Called