ints/v1) alongside user pushes.\\n   388→\\t// The remote parameter is the name of the remote being pushed to.\\n   389→\\t// Should return nil on errors to not block pushes (log warnings to stderr).\\n   390→\\tPrePush(ctx context.Context, remote string) error\\n   391→\\t// HandleTurnEnd performs strategy-specific cleanup at the end of a turn.\\n   392→\\t// Work items are read from state (e.g. TurnCheckpointIDs), not from the\\n   393→\\t// action list. The state has already been updated by ApplyTransition;\\n   394→\\t// the caller saves it after this method returns.\\n   395→\\tHandleTurnEnd(ctx context.Context, state *session.State) error\\n   396→\\t// RestoreLogsOnly restores session logs from a logs-only rewind point.\\n   397→\\t// Does not modify the working directory - only restores the transcript\\n   398→\\t// to the agent's session directory (determined per-session from checkpoint metadata).\\n   399→\\t// If force is false, prompts for confirmation when local logs have newer timestamps.\\n   400→\\t// Returns info about each restored session so callers can print correct resume commands.\\n   401→\\tRestoreLogsOnly(ctx context.Context, point RewindPoint, force bool) ([]RestoredSession, error)\\n   402→\\t// Reset deletes the shadow branch and session state for the current HEAD.\\n   403→\\t// Returns nil if there's nothing to reset (no shadow branch).\\n   404→\\tReset(ctx context.Context) error\\n   405→\\t// ResetSession clears the state for a single session and cleans up\\n   406→\\t// the shadow branch if no other sessions reference it.\\n   407→\\t// File changes remain in the working directory.\\n   408→\\tResetSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\\n   409→\\t// CondenseSessionByID force-condenses a session and cleans up.\\n   410→\\t// Generates a new checkpoint ID, condenses to entire/checkpoints/v1,\\n   411→\\t// updates the session state, and removes the shadow branch\\n   412→\\t// if no other active sessions need it.\\n   